STANDARD OUT (1) : 

    CREATE EMPTY FILE : > Filename

    OVERWRITE WITH REDIRECTION : echo New Message > Filename

    APPEND AT ENDING OF FILE WITH REDIRECTION : echo New Message >> Filename


STANDARD IN (0) :
    
    REDIRECT INPUT TO COMMAND : command < Filename


STANDARD ERROR (2) : 

    REDIRECT ERROR MESSAGES TO FILE : commands 2> Filename

    REDIRECT BOTH ERROR AND OUTPUT : commands &> Filename

    DISCARD ALL INPUTS : commands &> /dev/null


PIPE & TEE : 

    OUTPUT OF ONE COMMAND INPUT FOR ANOTHER : command_1 | command_2  | command_3 

    OUTPUT OF ONE PROCESS INPUT FOR MULTIPLE : command_1 | tee command_2 command_3


CAT : 

    READ FILES : cat file_1 file_2 file_N
    
    ADD LINE NUMBER : cat -n Filename


MORE : 

    READ FILE IN PARTED MANNER : more Filename


LESS :

    READ FILE IN PAGED MANNER : less Path/To/File

    QUIT LESS MODE : q

    SEARCH IN LESS MODE : /KeyWord

    
HEAD & TAIL : 

    SEE FIRST N LINES IN FILE : head -n N Path/To/File

    SEE LAST N LINES IN FILE : tail -n N Path/To/File

    SEE LIVE UPDATES AT ENDING OF FILE : tail -f Path/To/File


WORD LINE COUNT : 

    NUMBER OF WORDS IN FILE : wc -w Filename

    NUMBER OF LINES IN FILE : wc -l Filename

    NUMBER OF BYTES IN FILE : wc -c Filename

    ADD COUNT TO EACH LINE : nl Filename


SORT : 

    SORT BY CHARACTOR VALUE : sort Filename

    SORT REVERSE BY CHARACTOR VALUE : sort -r Filename

    SORT BY NUMERIC VALUE : sort -n Filename

    SORT UNIQUE VALUES : sort -u Filename

    SORT UNIQUE VALUES CASE INSESITIVE : sort -uf Filename

    SORT BY COLUMNN Nth VALUES : sort -k2 Filename


UNIQUE : 

    REMOVE DUPLICATE LINES : uniq Filename

    GET UNIQUE VALUES ONLY : uniq -u Filename

    GET DUPLICATE VALUES ONLY : uniq -d Filename

    GET DUPLICATE VALUES WITH DUPLICATES : uniq -D Filename

    OVERCOME NON ADJECENT DUPLICATES : sort Filename | uniq




